#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:523
msgid "Death of Krawg"
msgstr "Muerte de Krawg"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:381
msgid "Kawn"
msgstr "Kawn"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:400
msgid "I see a house in the distance!"
msgstr "¡Veo una casa en la distancia!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:415
msgid "Go away, you birds! Or I shall burn you out of the air!"
msgstr "¡Marchaos, pájaros! ¡U os quemaré en el mismo aire!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:419
msgid ""
"He doesn't want to talk to the gryphons, apparently. I think we'll have to "
"get someone there he will talk to..."
msgstr ""
"Él no quiere hablar con los grifos, aparentemente. Creo que deberíamos "
"mandar a alguien con quien quiera hablar..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:437
msgid "Thursagan"
msgstr "Thursagan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:443
msgid "What do you people want!? Leave me alone!"
msgstr "¿¡Qué quiere tu gente!? ¡Dejadme en paz!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:447
msgid ""
"Old mage, we come with a message from Lord Durstorn. He asks you to come "
"back to the city."
msgstr ""
"Viejo mago, venimos con un mensaje de Lord Durstorn. Os pide que volváis a "
"la ciudad."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:451
msgid ""
"Ha! That fool thinks he can order me around. Why does he want me to go back, "
"anyway?"
msgstr ""
"¡Ja! Ese tonto cree que me puede andar mandando. ¿Por qué quiere que vuelva, "
"de todos modos?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:455
msgid ""
"We have entered into a bargain with the king of Wesnoth to craft a sceptre "
"for him."
msgstr "Hemos acordado con el rey de Wesnoth en fabricar un cetro para él."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:459
msgid ""
"Oh, and now I suppose Durstorn wants me to craft it, eh? Well I'm not going "
"to."
msgstr ""
"Oh, y ahora supongo que Durstorn quiere que yo lo fabrique, ¿eh? Bueno, no "
"lo haré."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:463
msgid ""
"You don't want to make a sceptre to contain the power of the ruby of fire? "
"Very well, your choice is made."
msgstr ""
"¿No queréis fabricar un cetro para contener el poder del rubí de fuego? Muy "
"bien, has tomado tu decisión."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:467
msgid "The ruby of fire, what is that, some worthless Wesnothian gem?"
msgstr "El rubí de fuego, ¿qué es eso, alguna gema wesnothiana sin valor?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:471
msgid ""
"It is a Wesnothian gem, but it is also supposedly the most powerful magical "
"artifact ever seen. Even an untrained hand can use it to cast fiery bolts as "
"powerful as those of arch mages."
msgstr ""
"Es una gema wesnothiana, pero se supone también que es el artefacto mágico "
"más poderoso jamás visto. Incluso una mano inexperta podría usarlo para "
"emitir feroces rayos tan poderosos como los de los archimagos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:475
msgid "Oh, really? And what does Haldric want us to do with it?"
msgstr "¿De veras? ¿Y qué quiere Haldric que hagamos con ella?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:479
msgid "Contain and intensify its power."
msgstr "Contener e intensificar su poder."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:483
msgid ""
"I see. Fine then, I will help you craft this sceptre... into the most "
"powerful magic artifact ever seen. This will be a true test of my skill. I "
"expect it will take many years."
msgstr ""
"Ya veo. Bueno, os ayudaré a fabricar este cetro... el más poderoso artefacto "
"mágico jamás visto. Será una verdadera prueba de mi habilidad. Estimo que "
"llevará muchos años."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:487
msgid ""
"Good. Now, there are still wild animals here... we have to get back into the "
"caves."
msgstr ""
"Bien. Ahora, todavía hay animales salvajes por aquí... debemos volver a las "
"cuevas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:507
msgid "Move Thursagan to the signpost"
msgstr "Lleve a Thursagan a la señal"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:98
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:298
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:150
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:379
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:134
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:381
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:495
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:555
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:164
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:456
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:829
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:60
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:527
msgid "Death of Thursagan"
msgstr "Muerte de Thursagan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:545
msgid "Well, now we are in the caves again! Come on, back south, to the city."
msgstr ""
"Bien, ¡ahora estamos en las cuevas de nuevo! Vamos, regresemos al sur, a la "
"ciudad."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:3
msgid "The Council Regathers"
msgstr "El Consejo se vuelve a reunir"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:39
msgid ""
"The path back was less dangerous than it was a year earlier. It did not take "
"them so long. So they quickly returned to the dwarven city, with two new "
"members of their party - one expected, and one not."
msgstr ""
"La ruta de regreso era menos peligrosa que hacía un año antes. No les tomó "
"tanto tiempo. Así rápidamente regresaron a la ciudad de los enanos, con dos "
"nuevos miembros en su grupo; uno esperado, y otro no."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:121
msgid "Lord Durstorn, we have succeeded in our mission. Thursagan is here."
msgstr ""
"Señor Durstorn, hemos tenido éxito en nuestra misión. Thursagan está aquí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:125
msgid ""
"What? You mean you found Thursagan and got him to return with you? "
"Astounding! But what is that gryphon doing there?"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué? ¿Queréis decir que encontrasteis a Thursagan y lograsteis que volviera "
"con vos? ¡Increíble! ¿Pero qué hace ese grifo aquí?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:129
msgid "Yes, we did. And that is Krawg, who helped us in the northlands."
msgstr ""
"Sí, lo logramos. Y él es Krawg, quien nos ayudó en las tierras del norte."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:133
msgid "Yaa! Mee Krawg!"
msgstr "¡Siii! ¡Yoo Krawg!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:137
msgid "Now, where is this ruby that I am to work with, eh Durstorn?"
msgstr "Ahora, ¿dónde está ese rubí con el que debo trabajar, eh Durstorn?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:141
msgid ""
"In the treasury. And leave it there until you're ready to work with it - I "
"still don't trust you."
msgstr ""
"En la tesorería. Y dejadlo allí hasta que estés listo para trabajar con él; "
"aún no confío en vos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:145
msgid "Ha! _You_ don't trust _me_?"
msgstr "¡Ja! ¿_Vos_ no confiáis en _mí_?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:149
msgid ""
"Exactly! Why would I? And I order you to stay out of the treasury, away from "
"that ruby!"
msgstr ""
"¡Exactamente! ¿Por qué habría de hacerlo? ¡Y os ordeno que os mantengáis "
"alejado de la tesorería, lejos de ese rubí!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:153
msgid ""
"You don't dictate what I am to do, Durstorn! I will do as I please, and "
"don't stop me if you want me to make this sceptre."
msgstr ""
"¡Vos no dictáis lo que debo hacer, Durstorn! Voy a hacer lo que me dé la "
"gana, y no tratéis de detenerme si queréis que os haga ese cetro."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:157
msgid "The ruby is mine, and don't touch it!"
msgstr "¡El rubí es mío, no lo toquéis!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Uh, technically it's Haldric's, and I think that if Thursagan needs to see "
"to plan this sceptre, he can."
msgstr ""
"Eh, técnicamente es de Haldric, y creo que si Thursagan necesita verlo para "
"planear el cetro, debería poder."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:165
msgid "Fine. *grumble grumble*"
msgstr "Bien. *refunfuñando*"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:171
msgid ""
"Hm... a most interesting jewel. I can feel its magical power. I will start "
"drawing up plans for the sceptre immediately."
msgstr ""
"Hum... una joya más que interesante. Puedo sentir sus poderes mágicos. "
"Empezaré a dibujar los planos para el cetro inmediatamente."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:180
msgid "Now, I will need certain materials to make this sceptre."
msgstr "Ahora, necesitaré ciertos materiales para hacer este cetro."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:184
msgid "Oh, what?"
msgstr "Oh, ¿qué?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:188
msgid ""
"I would say probably ten stone of artifact-quality gold and twenty stone of "
"the finest coal, and many of the finest jewels in the land - we'll need "
"others to search for those, though. I'll also need to have the jeweler cut "
"the ruby once I have the plans done."
msgstr ""
"Yo diría probablemente diez pepitas de oro de calidad artesanal y veinte "
"piezas del más fino carbón, y muchas de las joyas más finas de la tierra; "
"aunque necesitaremos que otros las busquen. También necesitaré que el joyero "
"corte el rubí una vez que los planos estén listos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:192
msgid ""
"Just use my gold and coal, I have enough! Or, if they're not 'good enough' "
"for you, find them yourself."
msgstr ""
"¡Simplemente tomad mi oro y mi carbón, tengo suficiente! O, si no son «lo "
"suficientemente buenos» para vos, buscadlos vos mismo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:196
msgid ""
"You try my patience, Durstorn. You know yours aren't acceptable, but you "
"have to give me something or I can't make the sceptre!"
msgstr ""
"Ponéis mi paciencia a prueba, Durstorn. Sabéis que los vuestros no son "
"aceptables, ¡pero habéis de darme algo o no podré fabricar el cetro!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:200
msgid ""
"Wait, wait. The gold and coal... I think we can find those in the abandoned "
"eastern mines. Trolls have overrun them, but earlier they were the source of "
"the finest smithing materials."
msgstr ""
"Esperad, esperad. El oro y el carbón... creo que los podemos encontrar en "
"las minas abandonadas del este. Los trolls las han avasallado, pero solían "
"ser la fuente de los mejores materiales de artesanía."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:204
msgid "So, we will go to the eastern mines!"
msgstr "¡Pues, iremos a las minas del este!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Fine. As for the jewels, I will have others obtain those. That will cost "
"quite a bit of our payment, but it can't be helped. Our people do not mine "
"jewels."
msgstr ""
"Bien. Y con respecto a las joyas, haré que otros las consigan. Eso nos va a "
"costar una buena parte de nuestra paga, pero no hay nada que hacer. Nuestra "
"gente no produce joyas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:212
msgid ""
"That is acceptable. Durstorn, send some miners along with us to the Eastern "
"Mines, and I will bring some runecrafters-in-training from the academy to "
"help fight these enemies."
msgstr ""
"Es aceptable, Durstorn, mandad algunos mineros junto con nosotros a las "
"Minas del Este, y traeré algunos artesanos rúnicos aprendices de la academia "
"para que ayuden a luchar contra los enemigos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:219
msgid "Kinan"
msgstr "Kinan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:225
msgid "Rynan"
msgstr "Rynan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:228
msgid "Two runesmiths from the academy have joined you!"
msgstr "¡Dos herreros rúnicos de la academia se han unido a usted!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:233
msgid ""
"Fine, you all go to the eastern mines. Me, I'll stay here. No point going "
"where I can't help!"
msgstr ""
"Bien, id todos a las minas del este. Yo me quedaré aquí. ¡No tiene sentido "
"ir a dónde no puedo ayudar!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:238
msgid "M' 'u!"
msgstr "¡O misso io!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:3
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:11
msgid "Gathering Materials"
msgstr "Juntando materiales"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Those who went to the eastern mines were brave indeed. They were infested "
"with trolls and other vile creatures, who thrived in the dark and gloom of "
"the caves."
msgstr ""
"Aquellos que iban a las minas orientales eran ciertamente valientes. Estaban "
"infestadas con trolls y otras criaturas, protegidas por la oscuridad eterna "
"de las cuevas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:24
msgid ""
"And braver still were Rugnur and his companions, who had to spend two years "
"in those tunnels. For mining is a lengthy business. But they could for the "
"most part avoid the enemy. They only once had to venture into the very heart "
"of the trolls' territory."
msgstr ""
"Y aún más valientes eran Rugnur y sus compañeros, quienes debieron pasar dos "
"años en aquellos túneles. Pues la minería es un trabajo largo. Pero pudieron "
"evitar al enemigo la mayor parte del tiempo. Sólo una vez se vieron en "
"necesidad de aventurarse al corazón del territorio de los trolls."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:48
msgid ""
"Bring the necessary gold and coal to create the sceptre to the chest near "
"the starting location."
msgstr ""
"Traiga el oro y carbón necesarios para crear el cetro al cofre cercano a la "
"posición de inicio."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:52
msgid "1 load of gold and 2 loads of coal are needed"
msgstr "Se necesitan 1 carga de oro y 2 de carbón"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:86
msgid ""
"Well, these are the eastern mines. Trolls and ogres live here, be prepared "
"to fight them; also be prepared to spend quite some time here - mining can "
"take a while."
msgstr ""
"Bien, estamos en las minas del este. Los trolls y ogros viven aquí, "
"preparaos para luchar contra ellos; también para pasar bastante tiempo aquí; "
"extraer los minerales puede llevar un buen tiempo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:90
msgid ""
"For me to make the artifact Haldric wants, I need a special type of gold. I "
"do not know where it was found, but Baglur said these mines were the source "
"of it."
msgstr ""
"Para fabricar el artefacto que quiere Haldric, necesito un tipo especial de "
"oro. No sé dónde encontrarlo, pero Baglur dijo que estas minas eran la "
"fuente de él."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:94
msgid "Also, the only coal that will melt this gold is also here."
msgstr "Además, el único carbón que derretirá este oro está también aquí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:98
msgid ""
"So we're down here to, what, mine this gold and coal? That should be easy "
"enough."
msgstr ""
"Entonces estamos aquí abajo para, ¿qué, extraer este oro y carbón? Eso "
"debería ser bastante fácil."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:102
msgid ""
"Yes, although we will have to hire the miners - they don't work for free. "
"But beware, there are trolls and such down here..."
msgstr ""
"Sí, aunque tendremos que reclutar mineros; no trabajan gratis. Pero cuidado, "
"hay trolls y demás aquí abajo..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:156
msgid "My load of coal is delivered!"
msgstr "¡Mi cargamento de carbón ha sido entregado!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:174
msgid "That's the last load of coal we need."
msgstr "Ese es el último cargamento de carbón que necesitamos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:184
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:236
msgid ""
"This is all we need from these mines. Now we should go back further west, "
"where there are no trolls and ogres, and mine there."
msgstr ""
"Esto es todo lo que necesitamos de estas minas. Ahora deberíamos ir más al "
"oeste, donde no hay trolls ni ogros, y seguir extrayendo allí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:212
msgid "Here's the gold."
msgstr "Aquí está el oro."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:332
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:457
msgid "Here is some of the coal that we need! Bring the miners to take it!"
msgstr ""
"¡Aquí hay algo del carbón que necesitamos! ¡Traed a los mineros para "
"extraerlo!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:346
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:471
msgid "I have all the coal I can carry..."
msgstr "Ya tengo todo el carbón que puedo llevar..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:522
msgid "Here is the mine of precious gold! Send the miners this way."
msgstr "¡Aquí está la mina del preciado oro! Enviad los mineros hasta aquí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:536
msgid "I have all the gold I can carry..."
msgstr "Ya tengo todo el oro que puedo llevar..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:3
msgid "The Jeweler"
msgstr "El Joyero"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:41
msgid ""
"Rugnur and his companions returned home. Now, I do not want to give the "
"impression that only Rugnur and Thursagan worked on this masterpiece. There "
"were others - many others. Thus I present Theganli, the jeweler. His role is "
"small, but an important one."
msgstr ""
"Rugnur y sus compañeros regresaron a casa. Ahora bien, no quiero que parezca "
"que sólo Rugnur y Thursagan trabajaban en esta obra maestra. Hubieron más; "
"muchos más. Así pues, os presento a Theganli, el joyero. Su papel es "
"pequeño, pero importante."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:120
msgid ""
"So, you have returned. I assume you have obtained the required materials? My "
"jeweler Theganli has spent the last two years buying jewels from some of the "
"northern clans. So now go to the forge and make your sceptre. What do you "
"need to annoy me for?"
msgstr ""
"Así pues, habéis regresado. ¿He de suponer que obtuvisteis los materiales "
"requeridos? Mi joyero Theganli ha pasado los últimos dos años comprando "
"joyas a algunos de los clanes del norte. Id entonces a la forja y haced el "
"cetro. ¿Para qué necesitáis molestarme?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:124
msgid "We don't. Not everything is about you. We need to talk to Theganli."
msgstr ""
"No lo hacemos. No todo tiene que ver con vos. Necesitamos hablar con "
"Theganli."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:128
msgid ""
"That makes sense, I guess you would to plan the sceptre's design... what in "
"particular do you want him to do?"
msgstr ""
"Eso tiene sentido, supongo que tendríais que planear el diseño del cetro... "
"¿qué necesitáis que haga él, en particular?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:132
msgid ""
"I need to make the plans for the sceptre, then have him cut the ruby to "
"match them."
msgstr ""
"Necesito hacer los planos del cetro, y luego hacer que el joyero corte el "
"rubí de acuerdo con ellos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:136
msgid "You're going to cut the jewel!? Are you insane?"
msgstr "¿¡Vais a cortar la joya!? ¿Estáis loco?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:140
msgid ""
"What are you talking about, sir? You knew all along the jewel would have to "
"be cut to make the sceptre out of."
msgstr ""
"¿De qué habláis, señor? Siempre supisteis que la joya debía ser cortada para "
"hacer el cetro."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:144
msgid "Oh... right, right. Fine. Theganli?"
msgstr "Oh... cierto, cierto. Bien. ¿Theganli?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:148
msgid "He's in his shop, in the southern tunnel."
msgstr "Está en su taller, en el túnel del sur."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:152
msgid "Whatever. Kuhnar, go, summon him here."
msgstr "Lo que sea. Kuhnar, id, tráedlo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:157
msgid ""
"Theganli! Come out of there, Durstorn orders you to come to the citadel."
msgstr "¡Theganli! Salid de ahí, Durstorn quiere que vayáis a la ciudadela."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:164
msgid "Theganli"
msgstr "Theganli"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:168
msgid "I'm coming... coming... stop pounding on the door..."
msgstr "Ya voy... ya voy... dejad de golpear la puerta..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:172
msgid ""
"He doesn't need to come here, I'll take the jewel to his shop. He'll need "
"his tools anyway."
msgstr ""
"No hace falta que venga aquí, le llevaré la joya a su taller. Va a necesitar "
"sus herramientas de todos modos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:177
msgid "Well, Theganli, what do you think of this jewel?"
msgstr "Bueno, Theganli, ¿qué pensáis de esta joya?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:181
msgid "Uh, um, yes, yes, very impressive jewel, impressive, yes... "
msgstr "Oh, hum, sí, sí, una joya muy impresionante, impresionante, sí... "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:185
msgid "Do you think you could cut it in the manner my plans specify?"
msgstr "¿Creéis poder cortarla como lo especifican mis planos?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:189
msgid "Well, uh, um, maybe... maybe... it will be hard... let me see..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, uh, hum, tal vez... tal vez... va a ser difícil... dejadme ver..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:193
msgid "Very well. See what you can do."
msgstr "Muy bien. Ved lo que podáis hacer."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:198
msgid ""
"Theganli spent many months cutting the jewels that would go into the Sceptre "
"of Fire, and the Ruby of Fire he attempted last. But he could not cut it."
msgstr ""
"Theganli pasó muchos meses cortando las joyas que irían en el Cetro de "
"Fuego, y finalmente lo intentó con el Rubí de Fuego. Pero no pudo cortarlo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:203
msgid "Well, do you have anything yet?!"
msgstr "Bien, ¡¿ya tenéis algo?!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:207
msgid ""
"Ah, well, uh, no... no, not yet... unfortunately... it seems... it can't be "
"cut... or scratched... or damaged at all... at least not by my tools..."
msgstr ""
"Ah, bien, hum, no... no, aún no... desafortunadamente... parece... que no se "
"puede cortar... ni rayar... o dañar de ninguna forma... por lo menos no con "
"mis herramientas..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:211
msgid ""
"So what do you propose we do? We need this jewel cut in a very specific way "
"to make sure... well, it doesn't matter why."
msgstr ""
"¿Qué proponéis que hagamos entonces? Necesitamos cortar esta joya de una "
"forma muy específica para asegurarnos de que... bueno, no importa el motivo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:215
msgid ""
"Well... maybe... the Shorbear clan? They have good tools... yes, yes, they "
"do..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno... tal vez... ¿el clan Shorbear? Ellos tienen buenas herramientas... "
"sí, sí, ellos lo harán..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:219
msgid "Who are they?"
msgstr "¿Quiénes son?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:223
msgid ""
"Another group... of dwarves... live south of here... above ground... yes... "
"best jewelers I know of... have special tools... tools, yes..."
msgstr ""
"Otro grupo... de enanos... viven al sur de aquí... sobre la tierra... sí... "
"los mejores joyeros que conozco... tienen herramientas especiales... "
"herramientas, sí..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:227
msgid ""
"Well, Rugnur, what are you waiting for? Go down and get these tools from "
"them, and carve the jewel!"
msgstr ""
"Bien, Rugnur, ¿qué estáis esperando? ¡Bajad y traed esas herramientas, y "
"tallad la joya!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:236
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:242
msgid ""
"We can't just go in there and take their property. We'll have to buy, or "
"rent, it from them."
msgstr ""
"No podemos ir y tomar sus cosas así como así. Tendríamos que comprárselas, o "
"alquilárselas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:248
msgid "Fine. Go rent it from them."
msgstr "Bien. Id y alquiládselas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:252
msgid "Very well. We'll go south now."
msgstr "Muy bien. Iremos al sur ahora."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:256
msgid ""
"Wait! Last time you made a bargain by yourself you lost us five thousand "
"pieces of silver. I'm going with you this time!"
msgstr ""
"¡Esperad! La última vez que regateasteis vos mismo, nos hicisteis perder "
"cinco mil piezas de plata. ¡Esta vez voy con vosotros!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:260
msgid "Are you sure that is wise, lord?"
msgstr "¿Estáis seguro que esto es sabio, señor?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:264
msgid ""
"Of course! To be safe, though, you and Noiraran are going to come with us."
msgstr ""
"¡Por supuesto! Aunque, para estar seguros, vos y Noiraran vendrán con "
"nosotros."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:268
msgid "Yes sir... *sigh*"
msgstr "Sí señor... *suspira*"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:3
msgid "Hills of the Shorbear Clan"
msgstr "Las colinas del clan Shorbear"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:36
msgid "Glonoin"
msgstr "Glonoin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:98
msgid ""
"All dwarves are known for a love of gold and a heart of stone. The shorbears "
"were no exception. They were crafters of crafters - they made tools. The "
"best in the land. And they bartered well."
msgstr ""
"A los enanos se les conoce por su amor al oro y sus corazones de piedra. Los "
"shorbears no eran una excepción. Eran los artesanos de los artesanos; "
"fabricaban herramientas. Las mejores de los alrededores. Y sabían negociar."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:118
msgid "Defeat dwarvish leader"
msgstr "Derrotar al líder enano"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:138
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:385
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:499
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:559
msgid "Death of Durstorn"
msgstr "Muerte de Durstorn"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:195
msgid ""
"Here we are; the hills of the Shorbear clan. What are we here for, anyway?"
msgstr ""
"Aquí estamos; las colinas del clan Shorbear. ¿Para qué estamos aquí, "
"entonces?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:199
msgid ""
"If I understand it correctly, we're here to bargain with the Shorbears, and "
"arrange for us to use their tools to cut the ruby."
msgstr ""
"Si lo entiendo correctamente, estamos aquí para negociar con los Shorbears, "
"y conseguir sus herramientas para cortar el rubí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:203
msgid "Exactly."
msgstr "Exactamente."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:207
msgid ""
"And I'll be doing the talking; I remember what happened last time you "
"negotiated a deal! We lost five thousand pieces of silver."
msgstr ""
"Y yo hablaré; ¡recuerdo lo que ocurrió la última vez que negociasteis! "
"Perdimos cinco mil piezas de plata."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:211
msgid "Ay, its some of them cave-dwarves. What business do you have here?"
msgstr "Oh, son algunos de los enanos de las cuevas. ¿Qué venís a hacer aquí?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:215
msgid ""
"I'm Lord Durstorn, king of my tribe. I have been told you are great jeweler-"
"workers, and so we come to rent some of your tools for a short time, a few "
"years at most."
msgstr ""
"Soy el Señor Durstorn, rey de mi tribu. Se dice que sois excelentes joyeros, "
"y por eso venimos a alquilar algunas de vuestras herramientas por un período "
"corto de tiempo, a lo más unos pocos años."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:219
msgid ""
"You're a king?! Must be a pretty small kingdom for you to come yourself to "
"bargain with us!"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Sois un rey?! ¡Debe ser un reino bastante pequeño para que vengáis vos "
"mismo a negociar con nosotros!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:223
msgid "You insult me! Do you want my business, or not?"
msgstr "¡Me insultáis! ¿Queréis hacer negocios conmigo, o no?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:227
msgid "Well, fine, I'll hear your offer."
msgstr "Bueno, está bien, escucharé vuestra oferta."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:231
msgid ""
"We'd like to rent your best tools for a short period of time. We'll only be "
"cutting one jewel with it. My starting offer is two hundred silver."
msgstr ""
"Nos gustaría alquilar vuestras herramientas por un corto período de tiempo. "
"Sólo cortaremos una joya con ellas. Mi oferta inicial es doscientas piezas "
"de plata."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:235
msgid ""
"It must be worth a lot for you to come this way and offer that much! How "
"much are you going to sell it for, eh?"
msgstr ""
"¡Debe valer mucho para que vengáis hasta aquí y ofrecezcáis tanto! ¿Por "
"cuánto planeáis venderla, eh?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:239
msgid "That's none of your concern!"
msgstr "¡No os incumbe!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:243
msgid "I'll take twenty-five hundred, minimum."
msgstr "Serán dos mil quinientas piezas, mínimo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:247
msgid "(whispered) Durstorn, that would be a quarter of all our profits!"
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) Durstorn, ¡eso sería una cuarta parte de todas nuestras "
"ganancias!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:251
msgid "I know that. Uh, Glonoin, how about five hundred?"
msgstr "Lo sé. Eh, Glonoin, ¿qué tal quinientas?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:255
msgid ""
"Twenty-three hundred is my lowest offer. I can tell I don't need the money "
"as much as you need the jewel cut!"
msgstr ""
"Dos mil trescientas es mi oferta mínima. ¡De todos modos no necesito el "
"dinero tanto como necesitáis cortar la joya!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:259
msgid "You must be mad! I'll offer one thousand, but no higher!"
msgstr "¡Debéis estar loco! ¡Ofrezco mil, nada más!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:263
msgid "Two thousand, and I'll go no lower!"
msgstr "¡Dos mil, y no rebajaré más!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:267
msgid "(whispered) What are we going to do? We can't go much higher!"
msgstr "(susurrando) ¿Qué haremos? ¡No podemos elevarla mucho más!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:271
msgid ""
"(whispered) Offer him fifteen hundred, but don't go up, even if he refuses."
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) Ofrecedle mil quinientos, pero no elevéis la oferta, aun si no "
"acepta."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:275
msgid ""
"(whispered) Bah! Getting this cut isn't worth that much; what with Rugnur's "
"mistake earlier, and all the other expenses, if we pay more than a thousand "
"we'll barely even make a profit!"
msgstr ""
"(susurrando) ¡Bah! Conseguir cortar eso no vale tanto; con el error de "
"Rugnur, y los demás gastos, ¡si pagáramos más de mil, apenas tendríamos "
"ganancias!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:279
msgid "(whispered) So what are you going to do?"
msgstr "(susurrando) Entonces, ¿qué planeáis hacer?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:283
msgid "(whispered) Fight him, and take the tools by force."
msgstr "(susurrando) Derrotarlo, y tomar las herramientas por la fuerza."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:287
msgid "Are you mad?!?"
msgstr "¿¡¿Estáis loco?!?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:291
msgid ""
"Of course not! Now, Glonoin; one thousand was my final offer. If you won't "
"accept it, we will take the tools from you by force!"
msgstr ""
"¡Por supuesto que no! Ahora, Glonoin; mil fue mi oferta final. Si no "
"aceptáis, obtendremos las herramientas por la fuerza!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:295
msgid "I'd like to see you try!"
msgstr "¡Me gustaría veros intentarlo!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:299
msgid "You're making a mistake, Durstorn."
msgstr "Estáis cometiendo un error, Durstorn."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:303
msgid "Shut up, all of you! Attack them!"
msgstr "¡Silencio, todos! ¡Atacad!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:313
msgid "Lyndar"
msgstr "Lyndar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:320
msgid ""
"Aha! I've spent years looking for you Dwarves, but now I've found you! "
"Prepare to die!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ajá! He pasado años buscándoos, enanos, ¡y finalmente os encuentro! "
"¡Preparaos para morir!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:324
msgid "Who the devil are you?"
msgstr "¿Quién demonios sois?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:328
msgid ""
"I thought we left the elves behind at the gates four years ago! It seems we "
"have two enemies now."
msgstr ""
"¡Creí haberlos dejado atrás en el portón hace cuatro años! Parece que ahora "
"tenemos dos enemigos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:332
msgid ""
"So, elves, are you against these dwarves too? They're attacking my clan for "
"absolutely no reason!"
msgstr ""
"¿Así que, elfos, estáis en contra de estos enanos también? ¡Atacan mi clan "
"sin motivo alguno!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:336
msgid "I see. So you don't have the ruby?"
msgstr "Ya veo. ¿Así que no tenéis el rubí?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:340
msgid ""
"No, they do. They wanted to rent my tools to cut it, but they didn't offer "
"me nearly enough!"
msgstr ""
"No, ellos lo tienen. ¡Querían alquilar mis herramientas para cortarlo, pero "
"no me ofrecieron lo suficiente!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:344
msgid ""
"How about this - I help you defeat them, and you let me keep the ruby when "
"we have?"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué tal esto; os ayudo a derrotarlos, y me dejáis conservar el rubí cuando "
"hayamos terminado?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:348
msgid "Deal!"
msgstr "¡Trato hecho!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:352
msgid "Ah, they don't scare me! We can take both of them!"
msgstr "¡Ah, no me asustan! ¡Podemos encargarnos de ambos!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:356
msgid ""
"Don't be a fool! We can't take the elves, and it was a mistake to attack "
"these dwarves, but if we have to fight we should retreat once we get what we "
"came for, the tools!"
msgstr ""
"¡No seáis tonto! ¡No podemos contra los elfos, y fue un error atacar a esos "
"enanos, pero si tenemos que luchar, deberíamos retirarnos una vez obtenido "
"lo que vinimos a buscar, las herramientas!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:361
msgid "Defeat Glonoin, the Shorbear clan leader"
msgstr "Derrote a Glonoin, el líder del clan Shorbear"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:365
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:479
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:539
msgid "Have all heroes in the Shorbear caves while no enemies are in the caves"
msgstr ""
"Tenga a todos los héroes en las cuevas Shorbear, y a los enemigos fuera de "
"las cuevas"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:427
msgid "Ha! Now we can get those tools easily, and go back to our own caves."
msgstr ""
"¡Ja! Ahora podremos obtener esas herramientas con facilidad, y volver a "
"nuestras cuevas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:431
msgid ""
"And how do you plan on doing that? There are elves swarming these hills, "
"trying to kill us."
msgstr ""
"¿Y cómo planeáis hacerlo? Los elfos han invadido estas colinas, y tratan de "
"matarnos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:435
msgid ""
"You are right... well, we will be able to break out eventually, and while "
"we're here, we'll be able to finally make the sceptre."
msgstr ""
"Ciertamente... bueno, podremos escapar finalmente, y mientras estamos aquí, "
"podremos por fin terminar de hacer el cetro."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:467
msgid ""
"Well, back to the battle - we are all in the caves, but there are still "
"enemies in here also!"
msgstr ""
"Bien, de vuelta a la batalla; estamos todos en las cuevas, ¡pero hay "
"enemigos aquí también!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:471
msgid ""
"Indeed. Kill them! And make sure no more enter. Then we can close the gates."
msgstr ""
"Ciertamente. ¡Matadlos! Y aseguraos de que no vuelvan a entrar. Luego "
"podremos cerrar las puertas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:511
msgid ""
"We have driven all of the dwarves and elves out of these caves. They are not "
"ours, though, and we can't stay here forever."
msgstr ""
"Hemos expulsado a todos los enanos y elfos de estas cuevas. No son nuestras, "
"sin embargo, y no podemos quedarnos aquí para siempre."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:515
msgid "True. I suspect these elves will try to besiege us here."
msgstr "Cierto. Supongo que esos elfos tratarán de sitiarnos aquí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:527
msgid ""
"Well, back to the battle - we need everyone to get into the Shorbear caves. "
"And then stop any enemies from coming in here."
msgstr ""
"Bien, de vuelta a la batalla; necesitamos que todos entren a las cuevas de "
"los Shorbear. Y luego detener la entrada de cualquier enemigo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:531
msgid "Indeed. Everyone to the caves, and kill those still inside!"
msgstr ""
"Por supuesto. ¡Todos a las cavernas, y matad a todos los que estén adentro!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:613
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:688
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:741
msgid ""
"We have driven all of the dwarves and elves out of these caves! Now, seal "
"the gates!"
msgstr ""
"¡Hemos expulsado a todos los enanos y elfos de estas cavernas! ¡Ahora, "
"cerrad las puertas!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:93
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:760
msgid "Gaanngh..."
msgstr "Gaanngh..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:3
msgid "Towards the Caves"
msgstr "Hacia las cavernas"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:30
msgid "Gaenlar"
msgstr "Gaenlar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:60
msgid "Glinan"
msgstr "Glinan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:87
msgid "Kalnar"
msgstr "Kalnar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:107
msgid ""
"Durstorn's rash action led to many problems. Not the least of which was "
"being surrounded by elves."
msgstr ""
"La precipitada acción de Durstorn causó muchos problemas. No precisamente el "
"menor era estar rodeados por los elfos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:110
msgid ""
"The dwarves spent several years trapped in those caves, the elves besieging "
"them. The dwarves could not leave, for there were far too many elves, and "
"there was no way out of the caverns other than above ground. But the elves "
"could not enter, for the magical dwarven gates were closed."
msgstr ""
"Los enanos pasaron algunos años atrapados en aquellas cuevas, con los elfos "
"asediándolos. Los enanos no podían dejar las cuevas, pues había muchísimos "
"elfos, y no había otra salida más que a la superficie. Pero los elfos no "
"podían entrar, puesto que las puertas mágicas de los enanos estaban cerradas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:113
msgid ""
"During this time, Thursagan crafted the Sceptre of Fire, first cutting the "
"jewel, then putting it, the gold and the cold steel into the heat of the "
"flame. The sceptre was crafted, but something was not right. No matter what "
"enchantment of runes he put on the sceptre, it did not fulfil its original "
"purpose."
msgstr ""
"Durante ese tiempo, Thursagan fabricó el Cetro de Fuego, primero cortando la "
"joya, y luego poniéndola, con el oro, y el frío acero, en el calor del "
"fuego. Estaba casi completado, salvo que algo no andaba bien. Sin importar "
"el encantamiento rúnico puesto en él, no cumplía su propósito original."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:130
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:367
msgid "Move Rugnur to the northeast cave entrance"
msgstr "Llevar a Rugnur a la entrada de la cueva al noreste"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:134
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:456
msgid "Move Alanin to the southern border east of the river"
msgstr "Llevar a Alanin a la frontera del sur, al este del río"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:181
msgid ""
"Well, Thursagan has reached a conclusion. He can't make the sceptre with the "
"materials he has here, but he has the final plans for it, and all the jewels "
"and gold he needs. Shouldn't we leave now?"
msgstr ""
"Bien, Thursagan ha llegado a una conclusión. No puede completar el cetro con "
"los materiales que hay aquí, pero tiene sus planos finales, y todas las "
"joyas y oro necesarios. ¿No deberíamos irnos ahora?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:185
msgid ""
"All this time and he couldn't make it? Fine, we should try to leave... but "
"it's not like we could leave if we wanted to. We're surrounded!"
msgstr ""
"¿Todo este tiempo y no lo consiguió? De acuerdo, trataremos de irnos... pero "
"no creo que podamos aunque queramos. ¡Estamos rodeados!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:194
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:204
msgid "If you'll permit me to say so, sir, you're wrong. We could - "
msgstr "Si me permite decirlo, señor, estáis equivocado. Podríamos -"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:198
msgid ""
"Shut up, Baglur! You don't know what you're talking about. I've analyzed the "
"situation, and we're doomed. Our best hope is to surrender. Perhaps if we "
"give the elves the plans for the sceptre they will let us survive."
msgstr ""
"¡Callaos, Baglur! No sabéis lo que decís. He analizado la situación, y "
"estamos condenados. Nuestra mejor alternativa es rendirnos. Si les "
"entregamos los planos del cetro a los elfos, quizá nos dejen vivir."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Shut up, Rugnur! You don't know what you're talking about. I've analyzed the "
"situation, and we're doomed. Our best hope is to surrender. Perhaps if we "
"give the elves the plans for the sceptre they will let us survive."
msgstr ""
"¡Callaos, Rugnur! No sabéis lo que decís. He analizado la situación, y "
"estamos condenados. Nuestra mejor alternativa es rendirnos. Si les "
"entregamos los planos del cetro a los elfos, quizá nos dejen vivir."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:214
msgid ""
"Yes, of course, let's just all be cowards! What happened to your honor, "
"Durstorn?!"
msgstr ""
"¡Sí, de acuerdo, seamos todos cobardes! ¡¿Qué ha pasado con vuestro honor, "
"Durstorn?!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:218
msgid ""
"You little fool, honor is less important than life! So, I'm ordering "
"Thursagan to give the plans and the ruby to the elves, as a peace offering. "
"Then maybe we'll walk out of here alive."
msgstr ""
"Chico estúpido, ¡el honor es menos importante que la vida! Así que ordeno a "
"Thursagan que entregue los planos y el rubí a los elfos, como oferta de paz. "
"Luego tal vez podamos salir de aquí con vida."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:222
msgid ""
"You don't have authority over me, Durstorn. And I wouldn't give the sceptre "
"to them even if you did. It's not yours to give, its mine, and Rugnur's, and "
"Baglur's. Krawg's done more for its existence than you have! And yet, you "
"still get the profits from selling it to Haldric."
msgstr ""
"No tenéis autoridad sobre mí, Durstorn. Y no les entregaría el cetro aunque "
"la tuvierais. No es vuestro para decidir, es mío, y de Rugnur, y Baglur. "
"¡Krawg ha hecho mucho más por su existencia que vos! Y además, aún tenéis "
"los beneficios de la venta a Haldric."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:226
msgid ""
"So what, all of you want to die? Fine by me, but I won't die with you! And "
"if you won't give the sceptre to the elves, I'll take it from you!"
msgstr ""
"¿Así que todos deseáis morir? Me parece bien, ¡pero no moriré junto a "
"vosotros! Y si no le vais a entregar el cetro a los elfos, ¡lo tomaré y "
"entregaré yo mismo!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:231
msgid " *swoosh*"
msgstr " *swoosh*"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:235
msgid ""
"Nice try, Durstorn, but you missed. Now, I'd say that attacking an ally "
"constitutes treason, wouldn't you?"
msgstr ""
"Buen intento, Durstorn, pero fallasteis. Ahora, podría decir que atacar a un "
"aliado constituye traición, ¿no?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:239
msgid ""
"You're not my ally. You're more against me than the elves are; all they want "
"is the ruby, but you want us dead!"
msgstr ""
"No sois mi aliado. Estáis más en mi contra que los elfos; todo lo que "
"quieren es el rubí, ¡pero vos nos queréis muertos!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:243
msgid ""
"If that's what you're thinking, you're not fit to be ruler over us! So step "
"down, or we'll force you."
msgstr ""
"¡Si eso es lo que pensáis, no sois el adecuado para gobernarnos! Así pues "
"abdicad, u os obligaremos a ello."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:247
msgid "Never!"
msgstr "¡Jamás!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:252
msgid " *thud*"
msgstr " *bang*"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:261
msgid ""
"Well, I suppose we were right to silence him, but I don't like this. In any "
"case, now we should try to get out of here."
msgstr ""
"Bien, supongo que hicimos bien acallándolo, pero no me gusta esto. En todo "
"caso, ahora deberíamos tratar de salir de aquí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:265
msgid "Yes. So, see the area to the northeast of us?"
msgstr "Sí. Así que, ¿veis el área a nuestro noreste?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:275
msgid ""
"That's where there are the least elvish guards, so we have the greatest "
"chance of success there. I think we should try to get to it."
msgstr ""
"Ahí es donde hay menos guardias elfos, así que tendríamos más posibilidades "
"de salir por ahí. Creo que deberíamos intentarlo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:279
msgid ""
"This plan, it isn't worse than staying here to be killed, but it isn't "
"likely to succeed either. Even if it does, what will it accomplish? We will "
"be cornered there."
msgstr ""
"Este plan no es peor que quedarnos aquí para ser eliminados, pero tampoco "
"tiene más probabilidades de funcionar. Y aún si lo hace, ¿qué conseguiremos? "
"Seremos arrinconados ahí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:283
msgid ""
"I don't know if we will be cornered. That cave looks like it goes deep, and "
"we can lose the elves in the caves, they move so slow there."
msgstr ""
"No sé si lo seríamos. Esa cueva parece ser más profunda, y podríamos "
"despistar a los elfos en las cavernas, pues se mueven muy lento allí."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:287
msgid ""
"That's fine for you, you can run fast in caves, but I can't! What am I "
"supposed to do?"
msgstr ""
"Eso está bien para vosotros, podéis correr rápido en las cuevas, ¡pero yo "
"no! ¿Qué debería hacer?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:291
msgid ""
"Well, you are a member of the Wesnothian army. Why don't you rejoin it? See "
"if you can run past those elves to our southeast,"
msgstr ""
"Bien, sois miembro del ejército Wesnothniano. ¿Por qué no volvéis a éste? "
"Tratad de escapar de esos elfos a nuestro sureste,"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:301
msgid "And then ride south until you reach one of your outposts."
msgstr ""
"Y luego cabalgar hacia el sur, hasta alcanzar uno de vuestros puestos "
"fronterizos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:305
msgid ""
"I'm not going to do that, its suicide! And in any case, I've been with you "
"for 10 years, almost as long as I was in the Wesnothian army; I'd prefer to "
"fight with you."
msgstr ""
"¡No voy a hacerlo, sería un suicidio! Y de cualquier modo, he estado con "
"vosotros durante 10 años, casi tanto como estuve en el ejército de Wesnoth; "
"preferiría luchar junto a vosotros."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:309
msgid ""
"You going south has more of a chance of success for you than staying here or "
"going to the caves! And getting news to Haldric of what has happened is also "
"the best way to get help to us."
msgstr ""
"¡Yendo al sur tendréis más posibilidades de éxito que permaneciendo aquí o "
"yendo a las cuevas! E informar a Haldric de lo que ha pasado también sería "
"la mejor forma de ayudarnos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:313
msgid "I suppose..."
msgstr "Supongo..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:317
msgid "Come out, dwarves, and surrender! Or die in that cave, your choice."
msgstr ""
"¡Salid de ahí, enanos, y rendiros! O quedaros a morir en esa cueva, vosotros "
"elegís."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:351
msgid ""
"Alanin, ride as fast as you can south. Tell Haldric we are going into a "
"cave, and to send forces to help us as soon as he can!"
msgstr ""
"Alanin, cabalgad al sur tan rápido como podáis. ¡Decidle a Haldric que "
"entraremos a una caverna , y que envíe ayuda para nosotros tan pronto como "
"pueda!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:391
msgid ""
"I have made it past those elves, but they will chase me, and elvish horses "
"are faster than mine."
msgstr ""
"He conseguido pasar tras esos elfos, pero me perseguirán, y los caballos "
"élficos son más rápidos que el mío."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:421
msgid "Rugnur, I am going south. What should I tell Haldric?"
msgstr "Rugnur, voy al sur. ¿Qué debería decirle a Haldric?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:425
msgid ""
"Tell him to send forces north to aid us and fight the elves, but that we are "
"probably going to die. We are going into the caves."
msgstr ""
"Decidle que envíe fuerzas al norte para ayudarnos a luchar contra los elfos, "
"pero que probablemente moriremos. Entraremos a las cavernas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:472
msgid ""
"I don't know what is in these caves, but whatever it is can't be worse than "
"staying here to die."
msgstr ""
"No sé que habrá en esas cavernas, pero no puede ser peor que quedarnos aquí "
"a morir."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:3
msgid "Outriding the Outriders"
msgstr "Escapando de los jinetes"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:57
msgid ""
"Rugnur had fled to the caves, but Alanin could not do that. He went south - "
"back to the Wesnoth border."
msgstr ""
"Rugnur huyó a las cuevas, pero Alanin no podía hacer tal cosa. Fue al sur; "
"de vuelta a la frontera con Wesnoth."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:60
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The elves followed both of them. First I will tell of their persuit of "
"Alanin, before we descend into the caves to learn Rugnur's fate."
msgstr ""
"Los elfos los persiguieron a ambos. Primero, relataré su persecución tras "
"Alanin, antes de que descendamos a las cavernas a conocer el destino de "
"Rugnur."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:77
msgid "Reach the Wesnothian outpost in the south"
msgstr "Alcanzar el puesto fronterizo Wesnothniano en el sur"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:100
msgid ""
"Well, the elves are behind me for now, but they will send riders to catch "
"me, and elvish riders are faster than me."
msgstr ""
"Bien, he dejado atrás a los elfos por ahora, pero enviarán jinetes a "
"alcanzarme, y sus jinetes son más rápidos que yo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:104
msgid ""
"My only hope is to convince the peasants to stop the elves from passing "
"through their land, so I can get ahead of them."
msgstr ""
"Mi única esperanza es convencer a los campesinos para que impidan a los los "
"elfos atravesar sus tierras, para que pueda alejarme de ellos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:113
msgid "Lord Asaeri"
msgstr "Lord Asaeri"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:124
msgid "Gaelir"
msgstr "Gaelir"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:135
msgid "Salira"
msgstr "Salira"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:146
msgid "Losnin"
msgstr "Losnin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:157
msgid "Ealin"
msgstr "Ealin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:173
msgid ""
"You cannot outride us, horseman of Wesnoth! Whatever message you are "
"carrying, it will not be delivered!"
msgstr ""
"¡No podéis escapar de nosotros, jinete de Wesnoth! ¡Sea cual sea el mensaje "
"que lleváis, no será entregado!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:177
msgid "We shall see about that!"
msgstr "¡Ya lo veremos!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:186
msgid "Raesil"
msgstr "Raesil"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:203
msgid ""
"The villagers here are loyal to Wesnoth. They should be willing to help me "
"escape these elves!"
msgstr ""
"Los aldeanos de aquí son leales a Wesnoth. ¡Deberían aceptar ayudarme a "
"escapar de esos elfos!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:208
msgid "Rolin"
msgstr "Rolin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:213
msgid "We will certainly help any warrior of Wesnoth who needs our help!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ciertamente ayudaremos a cualquier guerrero de Wesnoth que necesite nuestra "
"ayuda!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:240
msgid "Hadlin"
msgstr "Hadlin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:245
msgid "Who goes there?"
msgstr "¿Quién hay ahí?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:249
msgid ""
"I'm a dragoon, with Haldric II's personal bodyguard. I was sent on a mission "
"in the northlands, and now elvish horsemen are chasing me. I barely evaded "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Soy un dragón de la guardia personal de Haldric II. Fui enviado a una misión "
"en las tierras del norte, y ahora jinetes elfos me persiguen. Apenas he "
"conseguido evadirlos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:253
msgid ""
"I see. Well, come on in. I doubt they would be able to capture this fort, "
"even if they did want to start a war, which I doubt."
msgstr ""
"Ya veo. Bien, venid. Dudo que puedan tomar esta fortaleza, incluso si "
"quisieran iniciar una guerra, lo cual dudo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:3
msgid "The Dragon"
msgstr "El dragón"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:32
msgid "Landar"
msgstr "Landar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:51
msgid "Khrakrahs"
msgstr "Khrakrahs"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:69
msgid ""
"Thus Alanin escaped from his Elvish pursuers. But the dwarves were not so "
"lucky. I would say that, perhaps, their betrayal of Durstorn was coming back "
"to haunt them. For unknown to them, they had entered the caves of "
"Khrakhrahs... the dragon."
msgstr ""
"Y así, Alanin escapó de sus perseguidores élficos. Pero los enanos no fueron "
"tan afortunados. Diría que, quizá, su traición a Durstorn los maldijo. Sin "
"saberlo, habían entrado a las cavernas de Khrakhrahs... el dragón."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:86
msgid "Get all heroes to the end of the tunnel"
msgstr "Llevar a todos los héroes al final del túnel"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:186
msgid ""
"Well, Thursagan, we've reached the caves, but the elves are hot on our "
"trail. What do we do now?"
msgstr ""
"Bien, Thursagan, hemos alcanzado las cavernas, pero los elfos nos pisan los "
"talones. ¿Qué haremos ahora?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:190
msgid ""
"Well, we have two choices. We may either stand and fight, and assuredly die, "
"or run as quickly as possible down this path into the depths of the cave, "
"where we may find something that will help us. Also, remember, the elves "
"can't run as fast in caves as we can, so we may be able to get ahead of them "
"and perhaps lay a trap."
msgstr ""
"Bien, tenemos dos opciones. Podemos quedarnos a luchar, y seguramente morir, "
"o correr tan rápido como nos sea posible a las profundidades de la caverna, "
"donde quizá encontremos algo que nos ayude. Además, recordad que los elfos "
"no pueden correr tan rápido en las cuevas como nosotros, así que podríamos "
"perderlos, y quizá prepararles una trampa."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:194
msgid "Why don't we just surrender? All they want is that magic stone!"
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué no simplemente nos rendimos? ¡Todo lo que quieren es esa piedra "
"mágica!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:198
msgid ""
"If we give them the ruby, then what? They'll probably kill us anyway. And, "
"that ruby has the power to do great things, evil things. We can't let it "
"fall into the wrong hands."
msgstr ""
"Y si les entregamos el rubí, ¿después qué? Seguramente nos matarían de todos "
"modos. Y, ese rubí tiene el poder para hacer grandes cosas, cosas malas. No "
"podemos dejar que caiga en malas manos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:207
msgid ""
"So we're running away, eh? I don't like that, but it seems it's our only "
"option."
msgstr ""
"¿Así que estamos escapando, eh? No me gusta, pero parece ser nuestra única "
"opción."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:211
msgid "If it makes you feel any better, we'll probably die this way, too."
msgstr "Si os hace sentir mejor, posiblemente moriremos de este modo, también."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:224
msgid "Look, there's a dragon in these caves!"
msgstr "¡Mirad, hay un dragón en estas cuevas!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:228
msgid "Ah, fresh meat!"
msgstr "¡Ah, carne fresca!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:232
msgid "And which of the great dragons are you?"
msgstr "¿Y cuál de los grandes dragones sois vos?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:236
msgid ""
"I am Khrakrahs, greatest dragon of all time! Haldric killed Shek'kahan my "
"brother, but he was weaker than me, and you will not find me so easy to "
"defeat. Now get out of my volcano!"
msgstr ""
"Soy Khrakrahs, el mayor dragón de todos los tiempos! Haldric asesinó a mi "
"hermano Shek'kahan, pero él era más débil que yo, no soy tan fácil de "
"derrotar. Ahora, ¡salid de mi volcán!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:240
msgid ""
"I'd rather face one powerful dragon than hundreds of mighty elves. Continue!"
msgstr ""
"Preferiría enfrentarme a un poderoso dragón que a cientos de poderosos "
"elfos. ¡Continuad!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:252
msgid "What's this? A dwarf fighting against us with the elves?!"
msgstr "¿Qué es esto? ¡¿Un enano luchando contra nosotros junto a los elfos?!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:256
msgid ""
"It must be one of those Surghan mercenaries. I'll bet those elves have hired "
"more of them. That's bad news for us, for they'll go as fast in caves as we "
"do."
msgstr ""
"Ha de ser uno de esos mercenarios Surghan. Apuesto a que esos elfos han "
"contratado más de ellos. Son malas noticias para nosotros, pues se mueven "
"tan rápido en las cuevas como nosotros."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:273
msgid ""
"Look, I've found something here. It looks like a forge, heated by the lava. "
"It looks magic, and it looks hot enough to make the Sceptre."
msgstr ""
"Mirad, he encontrado algo aquí. Parece ser una forja, calentada por la lava. "
"Parece mágica, y lo suficientemente caliente como para hacer el Cetro."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:277
msgid "That pretty metal rock is mine! Get away from it!"
msgstr "¡Esa preciosa roca metálica es mía! ¡Alejaos de ella!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:282
msgid "Move Thursagan to the forge"
msgstr "Llevar a Thursagan a la forja"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:286
msgid "Defend Thursagan until the sceptre is complete"
msgstr "Defender a Thursagan hasta que el cetro esté completado"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:316
msgid ""
"This forge will work perfectly. Give me a few days here, and I can reforge "
"the sceptre to fulfil its purpose."
msgstr ""
"Esta forja será perfecta. Dadme unos pocos días, y podré forjar de nuevo el "
"cetro para que cumpla su propósito."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:325
msgid "Survive for 9 turns"
msgstr "Sobrevivir durante 9 turnos"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:337
msgid "An enemy moves onto the forge"
msgstr "Que un enemigo alcance la forja"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:362
msgid "You fool, you let the enemy get at me as I was unarmed!"
msgstr "¡Idiota, habéis dejado al enemigo alcanzarme estando desarmado!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:116
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:368
msgid "Ayahahh..."
msgstr "Ayahahh..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:392
msgid ""
"I have completed my work. Now it is truly the Sceptre of Fire, a powerful "
"magical artifact."
msgstr ""
"He completado mi trabajo. Ahora es realmente el Cetro de Fuego, un poderoso "
"artefacto mágico."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:396
msgid ""
"Good. Now, let's get out of this cave, before the elves, dwarves or bats "
"kill us!"
msgstr ""
"Bien. Ahora, ¡salgamos de esta cueva, antes de que los elfos, enanos o "
"murciélagos nos maten!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:411
msgid "In $turnsleft more turns I will have completed the sceptre."
msgstr "En $turnsleft turnos más habré completado el cetro."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:3
msgid "Caverns of Flame"
msgstr "Cavernas de Fuego"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:130
msgid ""
"There was no exit from the caverns of Knalga. They had reached the realms of "
"the orcs, with the elves hot on their trail. And there was no exit from "
"those caves."
msgstr ""
"No había salida de las cavernas de Knalga. Habían alcanzado los reinos de "
"los orcos, con los elfos pisándoles los talones. Y no había salida de esas "
"cuevas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:133
msgid ""
"So the dwarves had no way out. They could not leave the caverns that they "
"had entered."
msgstr ""
"Así pues, los enanos no tenían escapatoria. No podían dejar las cuevas a las "
"que habían entrado."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:152
msgid "Explore as much of the cave as possible"
msgstr "Explorar tanto de la caverna como le sea posible"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:224
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:232
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:240
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:248
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:256
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:264
msgid "Guardian"
msgstr "Guardián"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:269
msgid ""
"Well, I think we've gotten a good distance ahead of the elves. What do we do "
"now?"
msgstr ""
"Bien, creo que nos hemos alejado bastante de los elfos. ¿Qué hacemos ahora?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:273
msgid ""
"We should keep going. Remember what Khrakrahs said, about this being a "
"volcano? I think we should try to cause it to erupt. It will kill all the "
"elves, and we might be able to find a safe place so the lava doesn't kill us."
msgstr ""
"Deberíamos continuar. ¿Recordáis lo que dijo Khrakrahs, sobre que esto es un "
"volcán? Creo que podríamos intentar causar una erupción. Mataría a todos los "
"elfos, y podríamos encontrar un lugar seguro para que la lava no nos mate."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:277
msgid "This sounds... attemptable."
msgstr "Suena... factible."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:281
msgid "Yes, an interesting plan. How do you propose we do this?"
msgstr "Sí, interesante plan. ¿Cómo sugerís que lo llevemos a cabo?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:285
msgid ""
"I have a suspicion that there is an opening somewhere near here than leads "
"to the surface. Somewhere near there, there is probably a magic object of "
"some kind that will cause the lava to flow."
msgstr ""
"Sospecho que hay una abertura cerca de aquí que lleva a la superficie. Cerca "
"de aquí, probablemente haya un objeto mágico de algún tipo que provoque que "
"la lava fluya."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:289
msgid "Very well. We will continue to explore until we find it."
msgstr "Muy bien. Seguiremos explorando hasta encontrarlo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:294
msgid "Krawg sme' o'cz in iz 'ave!"
msgstr "¡Krawg uel' orcz en 'tass 'vernas!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:298
msgid "Indeed, there may be orcs lurking here. We should beware of them."
msgstr ""
"Cierto, es posible que haya orcos acechando por aquí. Deberíamos tener "
"cuidado con ellos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:327
msgid "Aendan"
msgstr "Aendan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:333
msgid "We have caught up to the dwarves. Now, prepare to destroy them!"
msgstr "Hemos alcanzado a los enanos. ¡Ahora, preparaos para destruirlos!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:372
msgid "Thursagan! The elves are right on our tail; what should we do?"
msgstr "¡Thursagan! Los elfos nos pisan los talones; ¿que deberíamos hacer?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:376
msgid ""
"We could try to set off the volcano as soon as possible. Meanwhile, we "
"should draw the elves further into the caves, so they can't escape when it "
"does erupt."
msgstr ""
"Podríamos tratar de activar el volcán tan pronto como sea posible. Mientras "
"tanto, deberíamos tratar de hacerlos retirarse a lo profundo de las cuevas, "
"para que no puedan escapar cuando ocurra la erupción."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:435
msgid "These orcs appear to be guarding something."
msgstr "Esos orcos parecen estar protegiendo algo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:439
msgid "It is probably the magical object. Attack them!"
msgstr "Se debe tratar del objeto mágico. ¡Atacadlos!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:444
msgid "Move onto the glyph in the center of the volcano"
msgstr "Moverse hasta el glifo en el centro del volcán"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:507
msgid "That's it! The volcano will erupt soon now that you've triggered it."
msgstr "¡Eso es! El volcán hará erupción pronto, ahora que lo habéis activado."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:518
msgid ""
"Look, it has knocked down some of the walls! Those orcs have a way out now!"
msgstr ""
"¡Mirad, ha derribado algunas paredes! ¡Esos orcos tienen ahora una vía de "
"escape!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:527
msgid ""
"Well, we've succeeded in stopping the elves from getting the sceptre, I "
"would say. But what do we do now?!"
msgstr ""
"Bien, yo diría que hemos logrado evitar que los elfos obtengan el cetro. "
"¡¿Pero qué haremos ahora?!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:533
msgid "Now, we must fight the orcs until we die, it's our only option."
msgstr ""
"Ahora, debemos luchar contra los orcos hasta nuestra muerte, es nuestra "
"única opción."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:539
msgid ""
"We cannot let any of the elves or their mercenaries escape; they would tell "
"where the sceptre is. Make sure they all die!"
msgstr ""
"No podemos dejar que ninguno de los elfos o los mercenarios escapen; "
"revelarían la ubicación del cetro. ¡Aseguraos de que todos mueran!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:545
msgid ""
"We have to kill them quickly, before they realize what is happening. And "
"remember, the lava spreads quickly, suddenly, and dangerously. The only "
"place safe from it is the area near the glyph."
msgstr ""
"Tendremos que matarlos rápido, antes de que se percaten de lo que sucede. Y "
"recordad, la lava se desplaza rápida, brusca y peligrosamente. El único "
"lugar a salvo de ella es el área cerca del glifo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:577
msgid ""
"Wait, what's going on? The volcano is going to erupt! Everyone, try to get "
"out of these caves!"
msgstr ""
"Esperad, ¿qué sucede? ¡El volcán hará erupción! ¡Todos, tratad de salir de "
"estas cuevas!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:595
msgid "I must go report to my superiors!"
msgstr "¡Debo ir a informar a mis superiores!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:600
msgid "We have allowed an enemy to escape; we have failed."
msgstr "Dejamos escapar a un enemigo; hemos fallado."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:657
msgid ""
"Aghh!!! The volcano is erupting, and now our exit has been blocked off!!!"
msgstr ""
"¡¡¡Aghh!!! ¡¡¡El volcán está haciendo erupción, y nuestra salida ha sido "
"bloqueada!!!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:682
msgid ""
"We have hidden the sceptre well, but now the volcano is going to erupt and "
"kill us all."
msgstr ""
"Hemos ocultado bien el cetro, pero ahora el volcán hará erupción y nos "
"matará a todos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:817
msgid "Kill all of the elves before one of them escapes from the caves"
msgstr "Matar a todos los elfos antes de que cualquiera escape de las cuevas"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:924
msgid "Hm... Me le' no'w!"
msgstr "Hum... ¡iooirmee!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:3
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr "Epílogo"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:39
msgid ""
"And thus Rugnur died, a glorious death, in the eyes of the dwarven sages. "
"But our tale is not yet complete. For Alanin lived still, as did Krawg the "
"Gryphon."
msgstr ""
"Y así murió Rugnur, una gloriosa muerte, a juicio de los sabios enanos. Pero "
"nuestra historia no está aún completa. Pues Alanin vivía aún, así como Krawg "
"el grifo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:42
msgid ""
"Alanin traveled south, to Wesnoth, to Haldric II. To report the events of "
"the past fifteen years."
msgstr ""
"Alanin viajó al sur, a Wesnoth, a Haldric II. Para informar de los eventos "
"sucedidos en los últimos quince años."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:45
msgid ""
"And Krawg - well, Krawg followed him. I know not how. But Krawg made his way "
"south, to Weldyn, and reached it about the time that Alanin did."
msgstr ""
"Y Krawg; bien, Krawg le siguió. No sé como. Pero Krawg se dirigió hacia el "
"sur, a Weldyn, y llegó casi al mismo tiempo que Alanin."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:84
msgid "Guard Captain"
msgstr "Capitán de la guardia"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:101
msgid "Gatekeeper"
msgstr "Guardia de las puertas"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:117
msgid "Halt! What is your business in Weldyn, capital of Wesnoth?"
msgstr "¡Alto! ¿Qué os trae a Weldyn, capital de Wesnoth?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:121
msgid ""
"Stand aside. I am Alanin, of Haldric's royal guard, and I bring news from "
"the northlands."
msgstr ""
"A un lado. Soy Alanin, de la guardia real de Haldric, y traigo noticias de "
"las tierras del norte."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:125
msgid "Very well. You may pass."
msgstr "Muy bien. Podéis pasar."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:130
msgid ""
"I hear you desire to speak to the king, Alanin. What do you have to tell him?"
msgstr "Oí que deseáis hablar al rey, Alanin. ¿Qué tenéis que decirle?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:134
msgid ""
"I bring tidings of the Sceptre of Fire, commissioned fifteen years ago by "
"our king. I have been away for a long time, do not delay me even more."
msgstr ""
"Traigo nuevas del Cetro de Fuego, encargado hace quince años por nuestro "
"rey. He estado fuera por mucho tiempo, no me retraséis más."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:138
msgid "Enter, Alanin, and give the king your message."
msgstr "Entrad, Alanin, y entregad al rey vuestro mensaje."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:165
msgid ""
"My King, fifteen years ago you sent me on a mission into the northlands. I "
"have returned. What do you wish to know of my mission?"
msgstr ""
"Mi Rey, hace quince años me enviasteis en una misión a las tierras del "
"norte. He regresado. ¿Qué deseáis saber de mi misión?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:169
msgid "Well, was the Sceptre completed? Do you have it? Give it to me!"
msgstr "Bien, ¿fue el Cetro completado? ¿Lo tenéis? ¡Entregádmelo!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:173
msgid ""
"I believe it was completed, but, I do not have it. It is buried deep in the "
"mountains of the Northlands."
msgstr ""
"Creo que fue completado, pero, yo no lo tengo. Fue enterrado en lo profundo "
"de las montañas del norte."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:177
msgid ""
"Why? Why was it not returned to me? Have the dwarves reneged on their "
"promise, and kept it?"
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué? ¿Por qué no me fue regresado? ¿Acaso los enanos no cumplieron su "
"promesa y se lo quedaron?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:181
msgid ""
"My Lord, the dwarves are dead, slain by fire and smoke as lava poured out of "
"one of the mountains. I saw the eruption from afar as I was returning to you."
msgstr ""
"Mi señor, los enanos están muertos, asesinados por el fuego y el humo, pues "
"lava emergió de una de las montañas. Vi la erupción de lejos cuando "
"regresaba a vos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:185
msgid "Why were you returning without the sceptre, then?"
msgstr "¿Y por qué regresasteis sin el cetro, entonces?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:189
msgid ""
"We had been besieged by elves, in a dwarvish castle that was not Rugnur's. "
"The sceptre could not be completed there, but it could in a cave that lay to "
"the northeast of it. Rugnur sent me back, with the message that it had been "
"completed, but he and all the rest of the dwarves went into the caves, and "
"were immediately followed by hundreds of elves."
msgstr ""
"Fuimos asediados por elfos, en un castillo enano que no le pertenecía a "
"Rugnur. El cetro no pudo ser completado allí, pero sí pudo serlo en una "
"cueva al noreste de ahí. Rugnur me envió de vuelta, con el mensaje de que "
"había sido completado, pero él y los demás enanos bajaron a las cuevas, y "
"fueron inmediatamente perseguidos por cientos de elfos."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:193
msgid ""
"If the sceptre was not completed in your sight, what makes you so sure it "
"exists?"
msgstr ""
"Si el cetro no fue completado ante vuestros ojos, ¿qué os hace estar tan "
"seguro de que existe?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:197
msgid "I will let Krawg explain that."
msgstr "Dejaré que Krawg os lo explique."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:201
msgid "Who?"
msgstr "¿Quién?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:224
msgid ""
"My lord, a gryphon has just flown over our walls! It may be a sign of an "
"attack!"
msgstr ""
"¡Mi señor, un grifo acaba de volar por sobre nuestros muros! ¡Puede ser "
"señal de un ataque!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:228
msgid ""
"No, that is my... friend Krawg. He went with Rugnur into the caves, but "
"escaped through a hole in the roof right before the lava filled the cave."
msgstr ""
"No, es mi... amigo Krawg. Fue con Rugnur al interior de las cuevas, pero "
"escapó por un agujero en el techo, justo cuando la lava llenó la cueva."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:233
msgid "Ya, ya! Meh seah za zeptahur. Hrugnaar ha ee. Lozeet enda caav."
msgstr "¡Ssii, gii! Mí vee le ceerta. Hrughnaar teniio. Perdaao in acuuva."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:237
msgid "What the devil is he saying?"
msgstr "¿Qué demonios está diciendo?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:241
msgid ""
"He says that he has seen the Sceptre. Rugnur had it, but he lost it in the "
"caves. He came to tell you, so that you would know that the dwarves did "
"fulfil their promise."
msgstr ""
"Dice que ha visto el Cetro. Rugnur lo tenía, pero lo perdió en las cuevas. "
"Vino para decíroslo, para que supierais que los enanos cumplieron su promesa."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:246
msgid "Kreeeeya! Darat! Nomiduun. Bah."
msgstr "¡Eiiiaa! ¡Eco ie tood! Liito. Aiooo."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:250
msgid ""
"I see. Well... what do you want me to do now? The sceptre is made, yes, but "
"I don't know where it is, the makers are dead, and orcs have probably "
"already found it and hid it somewhere else."
msgstr ""
"Ya veo. Entonces... ¿qué queréis que haga ahora? El cetro fue completado, "
"sí, pero no sé donde está, los fabricantes están muertos, y probablemente "
"los orcos ya lo han encontrado y escondido en algún otro lugar."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:254
msgid ""
"I do not know. I only bring the news, I did not cause it, nor do I fully "
"understand its implications. But, my advice would be to do nothing. I "
"believe you will not find it, though you send a hundred armies to look for "
"it. But record in the history books that the sceptre does exist."
msgstr ""
"No lo sé. Sólo traigo las noticias, no lo causé, ni comprendo bien sus "
"implicaciones. Pero, mi consejo sería no hacer nada. Creo que no lo "
"encontraríais, aunque enviarais unos cien ejércitos a buscarlo. Pero que se "
"anote en los libros de historia que el cetro sí existe."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:258
msgid ""
"Your advice seems good to me. I will take it. As for you, and the gryphon, "
"you are free to go. Alanin, you've served in the army long enough to retire, "
"and even if you hadn't, you've seen enough combat. So, go. Back to your "
"village. You deserve a rest."
msgstr ""
"Me parece bien vuestro consejo. Lo seguiré. Y en cuanto a vos, y el grifo, "
"sois libres de iros. Alanin, habéis servido en el ejército durante el "
"suficiente tiempo como para retiraos, e incluso si no, ya habéis visto "
"suficiente combate. Así que iros. Regresad a vuestra aldea. Os merecéis un "
"descanso."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:262
msgid "Very well, my lord."
msgstr "Muy bien, mi señor."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:266
msgid ""
"The sceptre would not be found until many generations after Haldric II, in "
"the time of Asheviere the Dark Queen. During that time, it sat in the caves "
"of the Northlands, unfound but undestroyed, moved around by Orcs who never "
"understood its true power."
msgstr ""
"El cetro no sería encontrado hasta muchas generaciones después de Haldric "
"II, en los tiempos de Asheviere, la Reina Oscura. Durante ese tiempo, "
"permaneció en las cuevas de las tierras del norte, perdido pero intacto, "
"desplazado por orcos que jamás entendieron su verdadero poder."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:271
msgid ""
"But before it was found, legends grew up around it, and around its makers - "
"Thursagan, most brilliant of the Dwarven Sages, and Rugnur, the greatest of "
"the Dwarven Heroes of old."
msgstr ""
"Pero antes de ser encontrado, nacieron leyendas al respecto de éste y sus "
"fabricantes; Thursagan, el más brillante de los sabios Enanos, y Rugnur, el "
"mayor de los héroes Enanos de antaño."

